ou run","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"one command and get an isolated macOS VM ready for BlueBubbles — using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Apple’s official Virtualization framework, no Hackintosh tools required.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Why-a-VM-instead-of-bare-metal","text":"Why a VM instead of bare metal?"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Isolation","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — BlueBubbles needs Full Disk Access to read iMessage’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"chat database. Running it in a VM keeps it sandboxed from your daily Mac.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Snapshots","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — save a working iMessage configuration before macOS","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"updates, roll back if something breaks.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Dedicated environment","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — the VM can run 24\/7 headless while you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use your Mac normally.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Two servers","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — run two BlueBubbles instances (e.g., personal +","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"family Apple IDs) on one Mac using Spooktacular’s 2-VM support.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Quick-Start","text":"Quick Start"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"1-Create-a-VM","text":"1. Create a VM"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook create bluebubbles --from-ipsw latest \\","    --cpu 4 --memory 4 --disk 32 \\","    --network nat \\","    --user-data .\/setup-bluebubbles.sh \\","    --provision disk-inject"],"syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"BlueBubbles is lightweight — 4 CPU cores and 4 GB RAM is plenty.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"2-The-setup-script","text":"2. The setup script"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create ","type":"text"},{"code":"setup-bluebubbles.sh","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["#!\/bin\/bash","# setup-bluebubbles.sh — installs BlueBubbles server in a macOS VM","","set -euo pipefail","","# Install Homebrew","\/bin\/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/Homebrew\/install\/HEAD\/install.sh)\"","eval \"$(\/opt\/homebrew\/bin\/brew shellenv)\"","","# Install BlueBubbles server","brew install --cask bluebubbles-server","","# Enable Screen Sharing for remote management","sudo \/System\/Library\/CoreServices\/RemoteManagement\/ARDAgent.app\/Contents\/Resources\/kickstart \\","    -activate -configure -access -on -restart -agent -privs -all","","echo \"BlueBubbles server installed.\"","echo \"Connect via VNC to complete Apple ID sign-in and BlueBubbles setup.\""],"syntax":"bash"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"3-Start-and-configure","text":"3. Start and configure"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook start bluebubbles"],"syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The VM opens with a display window. Complete these one-time steps:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Sign in to your Apple ID","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — required for iMessage","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Open Messages.app","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — verify iMessage activates","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Launch BlueBubbles Server","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — configure your connection","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(Firebase, Cloudflare tunnel, or Tailscale)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Grant Full Disk Access","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — System Settings → Privacy &","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Security → Full Disk Access → add BlueBubbles","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"4-Run-headless-247","text":"4. Run headless 24\/7"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once configured, restart headless:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook stop bluebubbles","spook start bluebubbles --headless"],"syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The BlueBubbles server runs in the background. Access it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"remotely via VNC if you need to make changes:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook ip bluebubbles","# Connect via Screen Sharing to the reported IP"],"syntax":"bash"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Two-BlueBubbles-Instances","text":"Two BlueBubbles Instances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Run two iMessage servers on one Mac — one for each Apple ID:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook create bb-personal --from-ipsw latest --cpu 4 --memory 4","spook create bb-family --from-ipsw latest --cpu 4 --memory 4","","# Or clone from a configured base:","spook create bb-personal --from-ipsw latest --user-data .\/setup-bluebubbles.sh","# Configure Apple ID #1...","spook stop bb-personal","","spook clone bb-personal bb-family","# Start bb-family and sign in with Apple ID #2","spook start bb-family","# Configure Apple ID #2...","","# Run both headless","spook start bb-personal --headless","spook start bb-family --headless"],"syntax":"bash"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each VM gets a unique "},{"typ